##### FILE: base_linux.yaml #####

Applying 61 policy rule(s) to 1 resource(s)...

policy add-safe-to-evict applied to default/Pod/base_linux:
apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: base_linux
  namespace: default
spec:
  containers:
  - image: registry.k8s.io/pause
    name: container1
    securityContext:
      allowPrivilegeEscalation: false
      capabilities:
        drop:
        - ALL
  initContainers:
  - image: registry.k8s.io/pause
    name: initcontainer1
    securityContext:
      allowPrivilegeEscalation: false
      capabilities:
        drop:
        - ALL
  os:
    name: linux
  securityContext:
    runAsNonRoot: true
    seccompProfile:
      type: RuntimeDefault

---

Mutation has been applied successfully.

policy disallow-latest-tag -> resource default/Pod/base_linux failed:
1 - require-image-tag validation failure: validation error: An image tag is required. rule require-image-tag failed at path /image/

policy drop-cap-net-raw -> resource default/Pod/base_linux failed:
1 - require-drop-cap-net-raw validation failure: Containers must drop the `CAP_NET_RAW` capability.

policy add-safe-to-evict applied to default/Pod/base_linux:
apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: base_linux
  namespace: default
spec:
  containers:
  - image: registry.k8s.io/pause
    name: container1
    securityContext:
      allowPrivilegeEscalation: false
      capabilities:
        drop:
        - ALL
  initContainers:
  - image: registry.k8s.io/pause
    name: initcontainer1

      allowPrivilegeEscalation: false
      capabilities:
        drop:
        - ALL
  os:
    name: linux
  securityContext:
    runAsNonRoot: true
    seccompProfile:
      type: RuntimeDefault

##### FILE: base52.yaml #####

Applying 61 policy rule(s) to 1 resource(s)...

policy add-safe-to-evict applied to default/Pod/base:
apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: base
  namespace: default
spec:
  containers:
  - image: registry.k8s.io/pause
    name: container1
    securityContext:
      allowPrivilegeEscalation: false
      capabilities:
        drop:
        - ALL
  initContainers:
  - image: registry.k8s.io/pause
    name: initcontainer1
    securityContext:
      allowPrivilegeEscalation: false
      capabilities:
        drop:
        - ALL
  securityContext:
    runAsNonRoot: true
    seccompProfile:
      type: RuntimeDefault

---

      capabilities:
        drop:
        - ALL
  initContainers:
  - image: registry.k8s.io/pause
    name: initcontainer1
    securityContext:
      allowPrivilegeEscalation: false
      capabilities:
        drop:
        - ALL
  securityContext:
    runAsNonRoot: true
    seccompProfile:
      type: RuntimeDefault

##### FILE: base815.yaml #####

Applying 61 policy rule(s) to 1 resource(s)...

policy add-safe-to-evict applied to default/Deployment/nginx:
apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  labels:
    app.kubernetes.io/name: nginx
  name: nginx
  namespace: default
spec:
  minReadySeconds: 10
  replicas: 2
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app.kubernetes.io/name: nginx
  strategy:
    rollingUpdate:
      maxSurge: 1
      maxUnavailable: 1
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app.kubernetes.io/name: nginx
    spec:
      containers:
      - env:
        - name: DEBUG
          value: "true"
        image: nginx:latest
        name: nginx
        ports:
        - containerPort: 8080
        readinessProbe:
          httpGet:
            path: /
            port: 8080
        resources:
          limits:
            cpu: 250m
            memory: 256Mi
          requests:
            cpu: 125m
            memory: 128Mi

---

policy add-safe-to-evict applied to default/Ingress/service-a:
apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: Ingress
metadata:
  annotations:
    nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/auth-secret: server-a-secret
    nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/auth-secret-type: auth-file
    nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/auth-type: basic
    nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/rewrite-target: /$2
  name: service-a
  namespace: default
spec:
  ingressClassName: nginx
  rules:
  - host: public.my-services.com
    http:
      paths:
      - backend:
          service:
            name: service-a
            port:
              number: 80
        path: /path-a(/|$)(.*)
        pathType: Prefix

##### FILE: basic-example.yaml #####

Applying 61 policy rule(s) to 1 resource(s)...

policy add-safe-to-evict applied to default/Pod/liveness-pod:
apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: liveness-pod
  namespace: default
spec:
  containers:
  - image: nginx
    livenessProbe:
      failureThreshold: 3
      httpGet:
        path: /
        port: 80
      initialDelaySeconds: 10
      periodSeconds: 5
      timeoutSeconds: 2
    name: nginx-container
    ports:
    - containerPort: 80

---

##### FILE: basic-ingress1.yaml #####

Applying 61 policy rule(s) to 1 resource(s)...

policy add-safe-to-evict applied to default/Ingress/ingress-with-auth:
apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: Ingress
metadata:
  annotations:
    nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/auth-realm: Authentication Required - anvesh
    nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/auth-secret: basic-auth
    nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/auth-type: basic
    nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/rewrite-target: /
  name: ingress-with-auth
  namespace: default
spec:
  ingressClassName: nginx
  rules:
  - http:
      paths:
      - backend:
          service:
            name: blogging-svc
            port:
              number: 80
        path: /
        pathType: Prefix

---

##### FILE: basic-later.yaml #####

Applying 61 policy rule(s) to 1 resource(s)...

policy add-safe-to-evict applied to default/Pod/basicpod:
apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  labels:
    type: webserver
  name: basicpod
  namespace: default
spec:
  containers:
  - image: nginx
    name: webcont
    ports:
    - containerPort: 80
    volumeMounts:
    - mountPath: /var/log/nginx/
      name: weblog-pv-storage
  - env:
    - name: FLUENTD_ARGS
      value: -c /etc/fluentd-config/fluentd.conf
    image: registry.k8s.io/fluentd-gcp:1.30
    name: fdlogger
    volumeMounts:
    - mountPath: /var/log
      name: weblog-pv-storage
    - mountPath: /etc/fluentd-config
      name: log-config
  volumes:
  - name: weblog-pv-storage
